    "title": "Why OOH Media Owners Need a More Efficient Way to Manage Multiple Revenue Streams",
    "excerpt": "The evolution of OOH media buying methods means that the inventory is now consumed in a variety of ways – especially for digital screens. This includes loop-based, event-based, audience-based, impress...",
    "content": "<p></p>\n<p>The evolution of OOH media buying methods means that the inventory is now consumed in a variety of ways – especially for digital screens. This includes loop-based, event-based, audience-based, impression-based and other types of campaigns.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In our recent conversation with the weekender, some of our media partners shared thoughts on how they were able to manage inventories from a single platform and how it has helped them <a href=\"https://stg.movingwalls.com/blog/location-media-xchange-launches-revenue-management-suite-for-ooh-media-owners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"manage multiple revenue streams\">manage multiple revenue streams</a>. Hear from the likes of Ledtronics, Eyetalk Media Ventures, Laguna, and FC Media.</p>\n<p>Uncover the full article on Marketing Magazines WEEKENDER issue 334 >><strong><a href=\"https://issue334.weekender.marketingmagazine.com.my/?utm_campaign=WEEKENDER%202022&amp;utm_source=Weekender_2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Read More\">Read More</a></strong></p>\n<p>Location Media Xchange (LMX) is the supply-side technology arm of the Moving Walls Group. This <a href=\"https://stg.movingwalls.com/products/revenue-management-system/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"Revenue Management Platform\">Revenue Management Platform</a> enables&nbsp; media owners to optimise media availability across multiple sales channels including traditional sales teams, programmatic, open direct, and online self serve channels.</p>",
