    "slug": "moving-walls-at-woo-africa-2024",
    "title": "Moving Walls at WOO Africa 2024 ",
    "excerpt": "The World Out of Home Organization's (WOO) Africa Regional Forum was held on the 11th - 13th of March in Cape Town. This premier event brought together industry leaders to discuss the current state of...",
    "content": "<p>The World Out of Home Organization's (WOO) Africa Regional Forum was held on the 11th - 13th of March in Cape Town. This premier event brought together industry leaders to discuss the current state of the OOH industry and the trends for the future. </p>\n<p>The forum featured presentations and discussions by renowned industry experts.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Their insights shed light on critical issues facing OOH advertising in Africa, focusing on sustainability and the evolving landscape of the region.</p>\n<p>Mandakini Negi, one of the Co-Founders and&nbsp; Managing Director - of LMX was featured on the panel discussion on ‘Making OOH easier to buy through automation &amp; programmatic’ Her contributions highlighted Moving Walls' commitment to leveraging technology for enhanced advertising experiences.</p>\n<p>The forum provided a perfect platform for industry stakeholders like Moving Walls to collaborate, innovate, and plan how OOH advertising in Africa can move forward.</p>\n<figure><img src=\"https://stg.movingwalls.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/MW-Original-size-Feature-Images-10-1-1024x335.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13205\"/></figure>",
    "category": "Industry Trends",
    "author": "dinesh",
